text.tspan: | “What is Team Up?”
ITERATIONS 1
Paper Sketch
Mid-Fi
Hi-Fi
Another iteration on this screen was the
addition of “Go to Time out app”. From our
research, users did not know that Time Out
magazine has an application nor do they use
the app even though they were aware of it.
Since the application has been apart of the
business but users were unaware of it, we
wanted to raise awareness and engagement
to the existing application. As a result, we
added another CTA — “Go to TimeOut app”
so users are reminded that Time Out has a
mobile application. Also, it might been
convenient for some users to view it on the
app if it suits their preference.
Hence we changed Team Up to Invite
Friends, a straightforward CTA. “Add to my
wishlist” button has been added so users can
save the events they are interested in for
later reference.
In the paper prototype we named the CTA as
Team Up as we wanted to have a direct
association with the new concept Time Out
is launching. However, after the initial round
of user testing we found that users were
confused by the term “Team Up” and they
didn’t understand what the button does.
Therefore, we added an instruction on top of
the button to explain that you can “Team up
by inviting your friends”. Yet, users were still
reluctant to press the button as it was not
inviting.
